To verify async/await produces the same execution order as callback-based `next(err)` patterns:

**Minimal verification approach:**

```javascript
// Callback version
function callbackFlow(next) {
  step1((err) => {
    if (err) return next(err);
    step2((err) => {
      if (err) return next(err);
      step3(next);
    });
  });
}

// Async/await version
async function asyncFlow() {
  await step1Async();
  await step2Async();
  await step3Async();
